    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a bold take. i've heard some economists argue that trying to regulate them might actually backfire and end up hurting the smaller startups that rely on those same platforms to reach customers. do you think there's any real merit to that, or is the \"stifling innovation\" argument just something the big tech lobbyists use to avoid oversight?",
